Commentary Text: Arshdeep Singh to Shubman Gill, out Bowled!! Arshdeep strikes in his first over and this is a dream delivery - pitched up around off and nipped back in sharply, Gill was pressing forward on the defensive push, as he did so, he left a big gap between bat and pad - think the ball grazed the inside edge as it crashed into the top of off-stump. A pearler from young Arshdeep and he continues to impress on this IPL journey. Nothing much Gill could have done, perhaps he could have played close to his body, but you'd think you need to take chances in this format of the game. Shubman Gill b Arshdeep Singh 7(7) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Shivam Mavi to Rahul, no run, Tripathi is celebrating. But the umpires get together and decide to send it upstairs. If he has caught it, it's sensational work running in and diving forward. Okay the replays are in. But they don't seem to be very conclusive and the third umpire wants a zoomer. Still really hard to say. Are the fingers under the ball? There's no way a decision can be made with any certainty. Another angle called for. Such a big moment in the game. As you know with PBKS, control is a temporary thing. So much hinges on this and the third umpire is taking his time. It's a short ball at the body, Rahul pulls it flat to the deep where Tripathi comes charging in from the midwicket boundary. Okay we have a decision. The third umpire says it's touching the ground
